HEADWORD: Eelgrass
<hw>Eel"grass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
plant (<spn>Zostera marina</spn>), with very long and narrow leaves,
growing abundantly in shallow bays along the North Atlantic
coast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

